heaviest_rainfall.status: The heaviest total rainfall occurred on 04 January 2025, dropping 36.8mm of rain over the 37.2 hour storm duration with a maximum rate of 4.6mm per hour.

heaviest_rainrate.status: Today, the rain fell at an intense rate peaking at 16.2mm per hour, one of the heaviest downpours recorded and ranked 4th from our records.  The precipitation lasted 6.9 hours and dumped 9.36mm in total.  The rain rate reached 27.0mm per hour on 02 September 2025, and resulted in 21.19mm of rain over 15.0 hours.  This is the highest rate recorded by our weather station.

longest_rain.status: Rain fell for 37.2 hours on 04 January 2025 creating a new record that still lasts.  The storm produced a total of 36.8mm with a maximum intensity of 4.6mm per hour.

most_lightning.status: Since 11 April 2025, the day with the most lightning strikes is 07 September 2025 when 23 were seen.

nearest_lightning.status: The nearest lightning strike ever noted was on 13 May 2025, at 4.97 miles distance.

storm.status: There is a storm around.  It's the first significant stormy weather event since 13 September 2025.

top_10_rainy.status: We are in the midst of one of the longest rainy periods recorded.  This rainy period is ranked 9th since records began in 23 September 2024.  The current stretch started on 09 September 2025 and has lasted 6 days.  The longest rainy period started on 30 November 2024 and lasted for 10 days.

summary.description:
Today, cooler for the feels like temperature (down 2.8°C), outside temperature (down 2.5°C), and inside temperature (down 1.9°C) and more moisture-laden outside humidity (up 8%) and rainfall (up 0.1 mm).

Compared to today, yesterday also had noticeable differences in cloud levels (up 660 m), rainfall (down 0.1 mm), and light levels (up 5274 lux).

The past week and month had observable variation in cloud levels (up 1257 m), light levels (up 7218 lux), and rainfall (down 0.5 mm) when compared to today.
